10/06/2007
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Members of the Republika Srpska (RS) Interior Ministry detained Dragan Karadzic, the nephew of top war crimes suspect Radovan Karadzic, in Banja Luka Saturday (June 9th). According to a ministry spokeswoman, Tamara Despanic, police also questioned two of Dragan Karadzic's friends. All three were later released. Despanic said the move was part of efforts to locate the former Bosnian Serb leader, who is on the UN war crimes tribunal's "most wanted" list. (Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 10/06/07; NTV Hayat - 09/06/07)
